            <div id="track_leads" class="section">
                <h2>Track Leads</h2>
                <ul class="track-leads">
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Nels.png">
                        <h3>Nels Pederson <em>TCSW Cofounder and Director</em></h3>
                        <p>Nels Pederson is one of the original founders and current director of Twin Cities Startup Week. He has ran and worked with handful of early stage companies and fallen in love with the world of Entrepreneurship. Currently an associate with the Tech Stars Retail program. If he is not working he’s out climbing and exploring the world.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/http://www.beta.mn/" title="Beta.mn">
                            <img title="Beta.MN" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-beta-mn.svg" width="150px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Aaron.png">
                        <h3>Aaron Sykes <em>Disruptive Technology<br> Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Aaron Sykes is a Minneapolis-based unmanned aviation professional and advocate. Aaron founded Unmanned Standards to help companies leverage drone technology to increase workflow efficiency and accuracy and MAVMeetup to facilitate a collaborative community of 750+ responsible drone enthusiasts in the Twin Cities.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/https://www.meetup.com/Minnesota-Autonomous-Vehicle-Meetup/" title="Minnesota Autonomous Vehicle Meetup">
                            <img title="Minnesota Autonomous Vehicle Meetup" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-mav-meetup.png" width="150px">
                        </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Nick.png">
                        <h3>Nick Roseth <em>Tech Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Nick Roseth is Chief Operations Officer of SWAT Solutions, a solutions group focused on helping clients evolve their technology and quality ecosystems. Nick works best at the intersections of creative, technology, and business. As an evangelist for Minnesota, Nick is passionate about the MN Tech Community, is a connector of people and ideas, and is also the producer of DocuMNtary, a film about the story of technology in Minnesota.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/http://www.documntary.com/" title="Documntary">
                            <img title="Documntary" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-documntary.png" width="200px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Marty.png">
                        <h3>Marty Wetherall <em>Marketing and Advertising<br> Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Marty Wetherall is the Director of Innovation at Fallon where he works with clients to evolve the ways they engage with consumers. He’s also charged with developing new models and mindsets within the agency, fueled by his experience running multiple startups (including his summer at Y Combinator as co-founder of FanChatter) and exemplified by his creation of Fallon StarterKit (a venture storytelling program for cool crowdfunding projects with no up-front fee). Ask him what he thinks will happen next.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/http://www.fallon.com/" title="Fallon">
                            <img title="Fallon" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-fallon.png" width="100px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Danielle.png">
                        <h3>Danielle Steer <em>Impact Ventures Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Danielle is the manager of Operations and Member Services at Impact Hub MSP. Impact Hub MSP is part innovation lab, part business Incubator and part social enterprise community center offering purpose driven professionals a unique ecosystem of resources, inspiration, and collaboration opportunities to grow impact.</p>
                        <p>Impact Hub MSP is one of 82 locations supporting a network of over 16,000 change makers around the world who are addressing our communities more critical challenges in health, food solutions, technology, access, equality, and more.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/https://minneapolis.impacthub.net/" title="Impact Hub MSP">
                            <img title="Impact Hub MSP" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-impacthub.png" width="90px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Bharat.png">
                        <h3>Bharat Pulgam <em>Student Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Bharat Pulgam is currently a Freshman at the Carlson School of Management and passionate about connecting students with the incredible entrepreneurial resources available in the Twin cities community. Bharat started his own company during his sophomore year of high school with some help from a few friends Bharat also started a non-profit dedicated to breaking the stigma surrounding mental health which he has been working with since his Freshman year of high school. After coordinating Twin Cities Startup Weekend Youth earlier this year, he is excited to be the lead of the youth track for this year's TCSW.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/https://www.generation.mn/" title="Generation.mn">
                            <img title="Generation.mn" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-genmn.png" width="100px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Lauren.png">
                        <h3>Lauren Mehler Pradhan <em>Food and Agriculture Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Lauren Mehler Pradhan is the Director and General Manager of Grow North, a resource and connection hub for Minnesota's food and agriculture entrepreneurs and innovators. Lauren spent over 12 years in CPG brand management working on iconic brands and is passionate about changing the way food is grown, made and the impact individuals and start-ups can have in transforming our food system. Grow North is a part of the Holmes Center for Entrepreneurship.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/http://www.grownorthmn.com/" title="Grow North">
                            <img title="Grow North" src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/logo-grow-north.png" width="100px"> </a>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <img src="/web/20171006002238im_/http://twincitiesstartupweek.com/images/headshots/Connor.png">
                        <h3>Conner O'Brien <em>Healthcare Track Lead</em></h3>
                        <p>Conner O'Brien the Lead Organizer of Healthcare.mn – Minneapolis’ home for healthcare innovation where he helps catalyze and support 1, 800+ members of the healthcare innovation community, and connect startups with the resources needed for success such as mentorship, networking, and investment opportunities. He also serves as the Director of Sales &amp; Marketing for Inspiration Medical Technology and as an Ambassador for Hill Capital Corporation.</p>
                        <a href="https://web.archive.org/web/20171006002238/http://healthcare.mn/" title="Healthcare MN">
